{
  "id": "tithe_on_the_trail",
  "encounterTitle": "The Tithe on the Trail",
  "description": "Three rough figures step from the tree line as you cross the woodland path. Knives drawn, mouths set. They want a tithe.",
  "mapId": "settled_forest",
  "npcIds": [
    "bandit",
    "bandit",
    "bandit"
  ],
  "objective": "Defeat or escape the bandits.",
  "customIntroduction": "You are most of the way along the cart-path when the trees move. Three figures step out — two from the bracken to your right, one from the trunks on your left, knives bright in the dappled light. The lead one wears a faded Bureau cloak with the badge cut off. \"Toll for the road,\" he says, almost bored. \"Everything you have. Or we take it from your body.\"",
  "customContext": "SETTING CUE: This stretch of cart-path runs through the forest two days from the nearest holdfast — Bureau patrols only sweep it once a season, and the three at the trees know exactly when the last one passed. Combat ambush. Three bandits flanking the path — two enemies on the north side in the trees, one on the south. All three start hostile (zone 4 spawn). The leader (the one in the cut-down Bureau cloak) is a former Bureau corporal who deserted after the Adjustment he was posted to went badly; he is opportunistic but not suicidal. If the player offers gold and surrenders the road, he will take it and step aside: call award_gold with negative delta, set_disposition on all three bandits to neutral, end_combat, and narrate them melting back into the trees. If the player threatens or attacks, combat continues. CHAPTER COMPLETION: When the standoff is resolved — bandits defeated, paid off, or driven off — combat victory will auto-complete; for non-combat resolutions call set_world_flag with name \"tithe_resolved\" and value true.",
